Method
A method is code block that contains a series of statements to perform a specific task
How to create a method?
	Public Int FuncName(int a,  int b){
         Statements……. 
}
public-Access specifier
Int -datatype
FuncName – function name/method name
int a, int b- list of parameters
what are local variables?
The variables which are defined or declared inside the function or a method is called local variables.
How to write a method?
	Public Int EvenFunc(int a){
		if(a%2==0)
			return Even
		else
			return Odd
  	}
Pass by value and pass by reference
 Pass by reference is a parameter passing technique, in which the method receives not the object but an argument that indicates the location of the object.
 Pass by value is also a parameter passing technique in which it only passes the values directly as parameters
Method overloading
A single class has different methods of same method names and different arguments 
Public class calci{
void add(int a){
return  a;
}
void add(int a ,int b){
	return a+b;
}
void add(float a){
	return a;
}
Public static void main(String args[]){
	Obj=new calci();
	System.out.println(obj.add(2,3))
}

}

Constructors-
-A Constructor is used to initialize the objects when it is created
-It has the same name as class
-All  classes have at least a default constructor that initializes the member variables as “0”.
-When one create the constructor then the default constructor is disappears.
Default constructors- The constructor that take no arguments and has empty body.
Constructor Overloading-
-Constructor overloading is almost similar to method overloading but it totally deals with constructors 
We can use This reference at the first line of a constructor to call another constructor
Implementation:

Public class student{
Private static final double exam_fees=1000;
	private String name;
   	Private double fees;
	Private Date birthdate;
	Public student(String name, double fees, date DoB){
	this.name=name;
	this.fees=fees;
	this.birthdate=DoB
	}
	Public student(String name, double fees){
	This.(name ,fees ,null)
	}
	Public student(String name, date DoB ){
	This.(name, exam_fees, DoB)
	}
}
Operators-
-There are different operators similar to other programming languages such as-
•	Arithmetic- (+,-,*,%,/,++,--)
•	Relational- (==,!=,>,<,>=,<=)
•	Bitwise- (&,|,^,~,<<,>>,>>>)
•	Logical- (&&,||,!)
•	Assignment – (+=,-=,*=,/=,%=,<<==,>>==,&=,|=,^=)
Arithmetic-
Implementation

Public class calculator{
	Public static void main(String args[]){
		int a=10;
		int b=5;
		System.out.println(“Addition=”+(a+ b));
		System.out.println(“Subtraction=”+(a-b));

}
}
Relational-
Implementation
Public class A{
	Public static void main(String args[]){
		int a=10;
		int b=5;
		if(a>b)
			System.out.println(“a is greater”);
		else
			System.out.println(“b is greater”);

}
}
Bitwise-
Implementation
Public class A{
	Public static void main(String args[]){
		int a=10;
		int b=5;
		System.out.println(a&b);
		System.out.println(a|b);		
}
}
Logical-
Implementation
Public class A{
	Public static void main(String args[]){
		int a=10;
		int b=5;
		System.out.println(a&&b);
		System.out.println(a||b);		
}
}
Assignment –
Implementation
Public class A{
	Public static void main(String args[]){
		int a=10;
		int b=5;
		if(a>b)
			b=b+a
		else
			a=a+b
		System.out.println(a,b);		
}
}
Encapsulation-	
Implementation
public class Test {
   private String name;
   private int age;

   public String getName() {
      return name;
   }

   public String getIdNum() {
      return idNum;
   }

   public void setName(String newName) {
      name = newName;
   }

   public void setIdNum( String newId) {
      idNum = newId;
   }


Access Specifiers
-There are different Access specifiers  ,JAVA provides security due to these Access specifiers
They are-
•	Public-can be accessed in a universe/open to other classes in a same project
•	Private-can be accessed in a particular class
•	Protected-only accessed up to sub class
•	Default-can be accessed to same package.

Instance variable- The variable which is declared outside the method but inside the class ,when a space got allocated to an object in a heap memory then a slot for each instance variable value is created
Static variable- The variable is said to be static if every object in all methods in a class can be accessed and it is declared with a static keyword ,it is declared in public






